superset.name: uma_protection
superset.description: Provides permissions related to the User-Managed Access (UMA) protocol, allowing users to control access to their resources.

superset.name: superset_alpha
superset.description: Provides permissions related to the User-Managed Access (UMA) protocol, allowing users to control access to their resources.

superset.name: Gamma
superset.description: A predefined role for users with viewer-level access. Users can view dashboards and slices but cannot create or modify them.

superset.name: superset_granter
superset.description: Allows users to manage access and permissions, granting roles or permissions to others in the Superset environment.

superset.name: superset_sql_lab
superset.description: Grants access to the SQL Lab feature in Superset, allowing users to write and execute SQL queries on connected databases.

superset.name: superset_gamma
superset.description: Similar to the 'Gamma' role but tailored for specific configurations. Users with this role have read-only access to dashboards and slices.

superset.name: superset_public
superset.description: Provides minimal access intended for public or anonymous users, typically for accessing publicly available dashboards or views.

superset.name: superset_admin
superset.description: Grants full administrative permissions in Superset, including the ability to create, edit, and delete dashboards, manage users, and configure system settings.

policies.name: Account Management
policies.description: This permission allows users to manage their own accounts.
